  "texts": [
    "A similar, and similarly-sized, setting has been adopted in other recent LLM-related recommendation researches [56,57].",
    "To enhance the robustness and credibility of our results, we repeated the experiments three times, each with a different sample of 200 users.",
    "The average results and standard deviations from these trials are presented in Table 2.",
    "Baselines.We compare ToolRec 4 against two traditional approaches (the first two below), one that uses LLMs as RSs (the following one), two that enhance RSs with LLMs (the next two), and two that use LLMs to control RSs (the remaining two).• SASRec [22].",
    "A self-attention-based sequential recommender, which employs the encoder of the Transformer architecture to generate representations of users' behavior sequences."
